  "prompt": "What is the best WYSIWYG editor for Drupal 7?",
  "response": "For Drupal 7, some of the most popular WYSIWYG (What You See Is What You Get) editors are:\n\n1. **CKEditor**: This is one of the most widely used WYSIWYG editors in the Drupal community. It offers a rich set of features, including easy customizability and numerous plugins that can enhance its functionality. The CKEditor module for Drupal 7 integrates seamlessly with the platform, allowing you to add the editor to content types easily.\n\n2. **TinyMCE**: Another well-known WYSIWYG editor, TinyMCE can also be integrated with Drupal 7 via the TinyMCE module. It provides a user-friendly interface and various customization options. However, CKEditor tends to be favored for its robust feature set.\n\n3. **Wysiwyg module**: This module acts as a wrapper that allows integration of any WYSIWYG editor, such as CKEditor or TinyMCE, with Drupal 7. It provides additional flexibility and customization options depending on which editor you choose to use.\n\nWhile CKEditor is generally recommended as the best option due to its features and support, the choice ultimately depends on your specific needs, preferences, and compatibility with other modules or themes you are using within your Drupal site. Be sure to check the documentation and community support for whichever editor you decide to implement.",
